edule-side changes. The daemon schedule format already supports `Output *OutputTarget` and `ToolCall *ToolCallSpec` in [example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go:41), and it passes `OutputTarget: schedule.Output` in [example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go:196) and [example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go:213). But the app writer currently creates only `{ id, agentId, agentName, prompt, enabled, pattern, scheduledAt, time, days, timezone, createdAt, nextRunAt }` in [scheduler.service.js](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/app/electron/services/scheduler.service.js:377), and executes only `executeAgent({ agentId, agentPath, prompt })` in [scheduler.service.js](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/app/electron/services/scheduler.service.js:355).\n\nOne more confirmed gap: the schedule struct in [example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go](/Users/user/src/github.com/example/agents/example/cli/internal/daemon/scheduler.go:31) has `ID`, `AgentID`, `AgentName`, `Prompt`, `Pattern`, `Time`, `Days`, `Timezone`, `Enabled`, `Output`, `NextRunAt`, `ToolCall`. It does not have `session_id` or `source_meta`. So if you want a delayed run to continue the same iMessage thread/session with full origin context, we would need to extend the schedule shape too.\n\nInference: the least disruptive path is to keep schedules in `schedules.json` for now and extend that schedule payload, rather than inventing a new schedules table in `metadata.db`, because both the app and daemon already share the file today."
